issue.title: Error of Loading Husky in My Own World File.

content.raw:
The error message means that the husky plugin could not be found on your computer. You will have to get and compile the plugin, see links below.

I recommend reading about husky [here](http://wiki.ros.org/Robots/Husky), and take a look at the code [here](https://github.com/husky).

You can also read about gazebo plugins [here](http://gazebosim.org/tutorials?cat=plugins).

issue.title: Error of Loading Husky in My Own World File.

content.raw: The husky code is not under our control. If you want access to the husky code, then you'll have to find the correct source online. Once you have the husky code, make sure you have a compiled plugin library that is in the `GAZEBO_PLUGIN_PATH` or `LD_LIBRARY_PATH` on your computer.
content.html: The husky code is not under our control. If you want access to the husky code, then you'll have to find the correct source online. Once you have the husky code, make sure you have a compiled plugin library that is in the GAZEBO_PLUGIN_PATH or LD_LIBRARY_PATH on your computer.
